ANKARA , November 12 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- <ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">Turkish State Minister Abdullah Gul reassured Iraq today that Turkey 's fight against the rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party -LRB- PKK -RRB- in northern Iraq is not aimed at breaking down Iraq 's territorial integrity</ENAMEX> .
Gul was speaking to reporters this evening after a meeting between Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan and Iraqi First Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz , who arrived here today for a one-day visit .
The Turkish state minister said the meeting discussed a series of issues including the territorial integrity of Iraq , the multi-party meeting on northern Iraq held in Ankara Iraq last month , the reopening of the Yumurtalik - Kirkuk petrol pipeline , and the struggle against terrorism .
Gul said , `` The U.N. sanctions against Iraq are detrimental to this region , but beneficial to terrorism . ''
The Ankara meeting was attended by representatives from the U.S. , Britain , Turkey , the Turkoman Front in northern Iraq , the Iraqi Patriotic Union of Kurdistan -LRB- PUK -RRB- and the Kurdistan Democratic Party -LRB- KDP -RRB- .
The two Iraqi Kurdish rival factions , Iran -backed PUK and the Baghdad -supported KDP , signed a peace deal following the meeting , pledging to maintain and strengthen the ceasefire in northern Iraq .
<ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">The PKK has been fighting a 12-year -old guerrilla war for self-rule , which has claimed the lives of more than 21,000 people including PKK militants , civilians and government troops in southeastern Turkey since August 1984 .</ENAMEX>
